1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:07,479
Server Guardian Warboard — built with Codex
and GPT-5.6 for OpenAI Build Week.

2
00:00:08,500 --> 00:00:12,820
Raw security logs are hard to scan, and risky to share.

3
00:00:13,070 --> 00:00:21,467
Server Guardian Warboard is a read-only viewer that turns
honeypot-style events from a live decoy server
into an explainable game dashboard.

4
00:00:21,717 --> 00:00:26,788
This is the public judging surface.
No account, and no write actions.

5
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:35,710
Privacy filtering happens in the backend,
before data ever reaches the browser.

6
00:00:35,960 --> 00:00:43,324
Source addresses become stable bot aliases.
Login names are masked. The protected host is generalized.

7
00:00:43,574 --> 00:00:51,318
Suspicious URLs and commands are defanged for safe display.
What you see here is everything the public can see.

8
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:59,014
The interface is fully bilingual.

9
00:00:59,264 --> 00:01:07,564
One click switches every panel, nameplate, and dialogue line
between English and Korean — including the canvas battle scenes.

10
00:01:07,814 --> 00:01:10,816
The choice is remembered locally in the browser.

11
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:24,017
Each view mode presents the same filtered event stream
for a different scanning workflow.

12
00:01:24,267 --> 00:01:30,930
The RPG village visualizes activity as a living scene.
The map view shows aggregate origins.

13
00:01:31,180 --> 00:01:38,043
And the NORAD view gives a classic operations-room overview.
All read-only, all privacy-filtered.

14
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:54,493
Deterministic demo scenes let judges evaluate
the experience even when live traffic is low.

15
00:01:54,743 --> 00:01:57,990
?demo=skirmish replays a complete battle.

16
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:08,833
High-risk payload events can even trigger first-person dungeon
sequences — three weapons, three distinct choreographies.

17
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:21,478
For Build Week, Codex and GPT-5.6 added the bilingual interface,
the privacy boundary, deterministic demos, and QA gates.

18
00:02:21,728 --> 00:02:30,072
Product, privacy, and design decisions stayed human.
The repository documents prior work vs. Build Week work.

19
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:38,500
A safer way to understand hostile automation,
without exposing the system it protects.

